sql:
SELECT AVG(gdp_per_capita) AS average_gdp_per_capita
FROM economic_freedom_index
WHERE overall_score > 60;

SELECT AVG(overall_score) AS average_overall_score
FROM economic_freedom_index
WHERE year_id = (SELECT year_id FROM years WHERE year = 2023);

external_knowledge:
- High economic freedom is often associated with a score over 80; 
- GDP per capita refers to the gross domestic product divided by the country's population, indicating the economic output per person;
- 'High level of economic freedom' here refers to an overall economic freedom score above eighty.

sql:
SELECT AVG(ei.gdp_per_capita) AS average_gdp_per_capita
FROM economic_freedom_index ei
WHERE ei.overall_score > 60.0;

SELECT AVG(gdp_per_capita) AS average_gdp_per_capita
FROM economic_freedom_index
WHERE year_id = 1;

external_knowledge:
- "leading countries in terms of economic freedom" refers to countries with the highest economic freedom scores; 
- "latest year available" refers to the most recent year in the database;
- "economic freedom metrics" are the economic freedom scores and GDP per capita.

sql:
SELECT AVG(economic_freedom_index.gdp_per_capita) AS average_gdp_per_capita
FROM economic_freedom_index
WHERE economic_freedom_index.property_rights >= 60;

SELECT user_id, submission_date
FROM data_submissions
ORDER BY submission_date DESC;

SELECT status, COUNT(submission_id) AS number_of_submissions
FROM data_submissions
GROUP BY status;

external_knowledge:
- 'northern part of the continent' refers to countries in the 'North America' region;
- 'recent past five years' refers to the years between 2018 and 2022;
- 'typical economic freedom rating' refers to the average overall economic freedom score.

sql:
